com.pump.graphics

Class BasicShapeInstruction

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pump.graphics.BasicFillInstruction
      • com.pump.graphics.BasicShapeInstruction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DrawInstruction, FillInstruction, GraphicInstruction, java.io.Serializable, javax.swing.tree.TreeNode

    public class BasicShapeInstruction
extends BasicFillInstruction
implements DrawInstruction, java.io.Serializable
    This paints a FillInstruction and then a DrawInstruction on top of it. This requires the shape, clipping, transform, and opacities of the fill and the stroke be the same. It is technically possible that the stroke or fill be null, but it is recommended to use the most appropriate instruction for each graphic operation.
